African Bank, AngloGold Ashanti, Exxaro: South Africa Stock Market Preview

-- B y   L a u r e n   v a n   d e r   W e s t h u i z e n
-- 
2011-06-16T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/african-bank-anglogold-exxaro-south-african-equities-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close. Yesterday was a public holiday in South
Africa.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index reversed two days of
gains, falling 228.84, or 0.7 percent, to 31,000.52 at the 5
p.m. close in Johannesburg on June 15.  African Bank Investments Ltd. (ABL)  : The South African
owner of a lender and a furniture retailer said it sold $300
million of five-year notes in its first issue of dollar-
denominated debt. African Bank lost 20 cents, or 0.6 percent, to
33.17 rand.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  : Africa’s largest producer
of the metal said a strike at its Cerro Vanguardia gold mine in
southern Argentina ended yesterday. AngloGold rose 35 cents, or
0.1 percent, to 292.50 rand.  Exxaro Resources Ltd. (EXX)  : The South African coal
miner is looking to invest in Zambia’s energy industry to supply
local mines and export to South Africa. Exxaro climbed 33 cents,
or 0.2 percent, to 166.93 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lauren van der Westhuizen at  at
 lvanderwesth@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
